      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic constitutive model with nonlinear geometry (large deformation) and frictional contact is appropriate for the compression-bending regime up to 40 mm displacement.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening elastoplastic model with von Mises yield criterion applied to Ti-6Al-4V screw and UHMWPE block. Large-deformation kinematics activated. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) between screw and rod. Model form consistent with published literature for metallic implant FEA under quasi-static bending."
